article.headline: Wright St. 76, Air Force 61
article.story: DAYTON, Ohio -- Vaughn Duggins scored 22 points to lead Wright State to a 76-61 win over Air Force on Wednesday night, snapping a four-game losing streak. Troy Tabler and N'Gai Evans added 19 apiece as the Raiders (4-5) jumped out to an 18-9 lead with 12:22 left in the first half and maintained at least a seven-point advantage the rest of the way. Evans scored eight points early in the second to lead the Raiders on a 13-0 run at the start of the half, taking a 53-28 lead -- their largest of the night. The loss snapped a four-game winning streak for the Falcons (5-2), who shot 22 for 36 from the floor (61.1 percent), but turned it over 20 times and allowed 20 second-chance points to Wright State. Derek Brooks came off the bench to lead Air Force with 13 points and seven rebounds. Wright State snapped a four-game losing streak with the win.
